{
  "stem": "27443.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was the second child.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Then I had my younger brother.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then just before the war in 1938, my youngest brother arrived.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And when they took us away, he was over a year old.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My older brother was Kasria Tuvia.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My younger brother was Moshe, and my youngest was Godel.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father's name was Schmuel Israel.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother's name was Hanna.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother's maiden name was Gassman.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father's name was Inowroclawski.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When the war broke out, I just finished my seventh grade of public school.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I beg your pardon?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My life was affected because my parents, just like any other parents today, have high dreams, high hopes, for their children.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I guess my parents had high hopes for me, too.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my schooling days were interrupted, and on the Hanukkah day, 1939, the second day of Hanukkah, the candles were on the table, and after midnight, our front door broke-- was broken in.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the Germans broke into my house, and they gave us 10 minutes to leave.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We gathered whatever it was possible in 10 minutes.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My mother grabbed the baby, and we're whatever-- whatever to take.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we were loaded up into trucks downstairs.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were taken to [?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Radogoszcz. ?] This was a big factory in Lodz, and we were gathered together with it-- in trucks.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "When we arrived over there, the place was already full with Jews, with children.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And when we arrived, we had nothing to eat and nothing to drink.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And early in the morning, we were gathered and lined up and loaded again into trucks, and we were taken to the trains.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it was always very big anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were always beaten or-- or taunted as Jews.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when the war broke out, it was terrible.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
